# Start Exploring the SmolNet

Want to start exploring the SmolNet, but haven't a clue where to start? This page is intended to help set you on the road!

This page covers what equipment you need, and points you at some useful search engines and other starting points.

!- TODO: Terminology (separate link) (gemspace, capsule, gemcap, gopherhole, glog, phlog, etc - be sure to differentiate between geminispace, and geminispace.org or whatever)

!-=> [web-failure link] What is SmolNet, and why should I care?

# Equipment

## Portals

If you're just testing the waters, then it's probably easiest to use your preferred web browser, together with a web portal that can translate between the Web and the SmolNet protocols (Gopher, Gemini, etc).

=> http://portal.mozz.us/ (Gemini, Spartan, Gopher...)
=> https://gopherproxy.meulie.net/ (Gopher only)
!- TODO: more portal links. Does geminiprotocol.net have some?

